# Development Workflow Rules

## Environment
- Node.js >= 20.19.0, npm >= 10.0.0, PHP >= 7.4, Composer, Docker (testing)
- Setup: `npm run prepare-environment`

## Main Repository Commands
- `npm run watch` - Development (builds packages + watches)
- `npm run build` / `npm run build:packages` - Build
- `npm run test:php` / `npm run test:jest` / `npm run test:playwright` - Tests

## Turbo-Repo Commands (cd packages)
- `npm run dev` / `npm run build` / `npm run test`
- `npm run lint` / `npm run check-unused` / `npm run format`

## File Structure
```
elementor/
├── app/, core/, includes/, modules/, tests/  (Main Repository)
└── packages/packages/{core,libs,tools}/      (Turbo-Repo)
```

## Workflow
1. Search existing functionality first
2. Understand if main repo or turbo-repo work
3. Follow existing patterns and conventions
4. Run tests and linting after implementation
5. Verify no circular dependencies

## Troubleshooting
- Reset: `npm run hard-reinstall`
- Force rebuild: `npm run build --force`
- Clear turbo cache: `cd packages && turbo build --force`
